<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="566" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d566">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/3314½</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-07">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 7, 1917</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Saw the Cuban Minister and advised him that it would be unwise for Cuba
                            to break off diplomatic relations with Germany. He said that he would so
                            advise his Govt</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>